ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: SKIP_PN INTERVIEWER: Skip section PN?

PN1 Have you ever had a spell or attack when all of a sudden you felt frightened, anxious, or panicky in situations when most people would not be afraid or anxious; that is, during times when you were not in danger, or were not making a speech, or something like that?
PNp1 Did you tell a doctor about these feelings?
PNp1a1 Did you tell any other health professional about these feelings?
PNp1b Were these feelings ever the result of physical illness or injury?
PNp1c Were these feelings ever the result of medication, drugs or alcohol?
PNp1d When you told the (doctor/health professional), what was the diagnosis? (What did the doctor/ health professional say was causing these feelings?)
Notes: 1=NERVES STRESS ANXIETY DEPRESSION MENTAL-ILLNESS;2=MEDICATION DRUGS ALCOHOL;3=PHYSICAL ILLNESS/ INJURY;4=NO DEFINITE DIAGNOSIS; -8 = DK AND REFUSAL

ElementDescription: PNp1g Did the (doctor/health professional) find anything abnormal by an exam, test, or x-ray?
PNp1h were these feelings always the result of physical illness or injury?
PNp1i When these feelings were not due to physical illness or injury, were they always the result of medication, drugs, or alcohol?
PNp1j were they always the result of medication, drugs or alcohol?
PNp1f When these feelings were not due to medication, drugs, or alcohol, were they always the result of physical illness or injury?
PNp1a3 Did these feelings interfere with your life or activities a lot?
PN1Probe
PN2a Have you ever had ...3 attacks within a three-week period?
PN2b (Have you ever had) ...4 attacks within a four-week period?
PN3 After having an attack, did you ever have a month or more when you worried a lot about having an attack or you were afraid that you might have another attack?
PN3a Did you think that having attacks like this must mean that you had a serious illness or that you were going crazy?
PN3a1 Did you think that for a month or longer?
PN3b Did having an attack like this cause you to stop doing anything that you used to do or stop going places you used to go?
PN3b1 Did you stop doing things or going places for a month or longer?
PN3b2 Did you avoid unfamiliar situations for a month or longer?
PN3b3 Did you avoid exercise for a month or longer?
PN3c After having an attack like this, did you begin to need someone to go with you?
PN3c1 Did that last for a month or longer?
PN4.1 During one of your worst attacks, did you have ...shortness of breath or feeling that you were smothering?
PN4.2 (During one of your worst attacks, did you have) ...palpitations or a pounding heart?
PN4.3 (During one of your worst attacks, did you have) ...dizziness, light-headedness, unsteadiness, or feeling faint?
PN4.4 (During one of your worst attacks, did you have) ...chest tightness or chest pain?
PN4.5 (During one of your worst attacks, did you have) ...numbness or tingling in your face, feet, or fingers?
PN4.6 (During one of your worst attacks, did you have) ...a choking sensation?
PN4.7 (During one of your worst attacks, did you have) ...sweating?
PN4.8 (During one of your worst attacks, did you have) ...shaking or trembling?
PN4.9 (During one of your worst attacks, did you have) ...flushing, hot flashes, or chills?
PN4.10 (During one of your worst attacks, did you have) ...a feeling that things were unreal?
PN4.11 (During one of your worst attacks, did you have) ...a fear that you might die?
PN4.12 (During one of your worst attacks, did you have) ...a fear that you were going crazy or losing control?
PN4.13 (During one of your worst attacks, did you have) ...nausea or discomfort in your stomach or abdomen?
PN5 You mentioned you had attacks of feeling frightened and some problems like (SX IN PN4.1-13). How many episodes have you had in your lifetime that had 4 or more of these problems?
PN5.1 Did you have more than one episode like this?
PN6 During at least several of your attacks, did some of these problems such as : (UP TO 4 SX CODED IN PN4) begin suddenly, and get worse in the first 10 minutes of the attacks?
PN7a Did you have attacks like that when you were in any of the following situations? (SOCPHOB SITUATIONS CODED 5 IN SP1.1-6)?
PN7b  IF ANY 5 CODED IN S2.1-5 (AGPHOB, p. 145), ASK: Did you have attacks like that when you were (AGPHOB SITUATIONS CODED 5 IN S2.1-5)?
PN7c Did being in any (other) particular situations make it likely that you would have an attack like this?
PN7d Have you had these attacks at times when you had no reason to expect one because you were not in any special situation?
PN_ao8 How old were you the first time you had one of these sudden attacks of feeling frightened or anxious when you had 4 or more problems like (ALL SX CODED 5 IN PN4.1-13)
PN_o8 (the first time you had one of these sudden attacks of feeling frightened or anxious) Was it within the last 30 days?
PN_ar8 How old were you the last time you had one of these sudden attacks of feeling frightened or anxious when you had 4 or more problems like (ALL SX CODED 5 IN PN4.1-13)
PN_r8 (the last time you had one of these sudden attacks of feeling frightened or anxious) Was it within the last 30 days?
PN_ao8DK IF DK ONS ASK: Did you first have one of these sudden attacks... BEGINNING WITH BEFORE YOU WERE 10 YEARS OLD, READ OPTIONS UNTIL R RESPONDS AFFIRMATIVELY
Notes: 1=before you were 10 years old?;2=before you were 20 years old?;3=before you were 30 years old?;4=before you were 40 years old?;5=before you were 50 years old?;6=before you were 60 years old?;7=before you were 70 years old?;8=before you were 80 years old?; -8 = DK AND REFUSAL
